    "body": "I'm thinking something like this:\r\n\r\n- phase 1\r\n  - testcases to be run in a kube cluster\r\n  - a single testcase, to be run run daily\r\n  - testcase has metrics and logs scraped from all running nodes (lodestar or not)\r\n  - metrics and logs get exported to an elasticsearch database, running separately, for later analysis, accessible to lodestar team, publicly if its not easily attackable/dos-able\r\n- phase 2\r\n  - dashboard(s) attached to elasticsearch\r\n  - testcases triggered by lodestar push/pr webhook\r\n  - additional testcases detailed and developed, added to scheduled runs\r\n- phase 3\r\n  - dashboard customized/tailored to show relevant high-level statistics\r\n  - hook into github checks API to push testcase results to lodestar PR statuses\r\n  - additional testcases!\r\n\r\nStart with simple testcases, spinning up small ephemeral testnets. The purpose of these tests is to quickly catch errors and measure baseline performance in \"live\" scenarios:\r\n1. baseline lodestar test\r\n- start N lodestar bn+vc, run for 10 minutes\r\n2. baseline interop sync and chain follow\r\n- start N lighthouse bn+vc, run 5 minutes. start 1 lodestar bn, let sync and run for 5 minutes",
